
[1]slop

   SLOP, v.t. [probably allied to lap.] To drink greedily and grossly.
   [Little used.]

   SLOP, n. [probably allied to slabber.]

   1. Water carelessly thrown about on a table or floor; a puddle; a
   soiled spot.

   2. Mean liquor; mean liquid food.

    SLOP, n. Trowsers; a loose lower garment; drawers; hence, ready made
                                  clothes.
